terraform:

HCL language 

terraform life cycle:

code (config file) -> init (initialise project) -> plan -> validate ( happens automatically) -> execute ( terraform apply) -> terraform destroy 


change automation:
execution plans and resource graphs for change automation 

execution plans: manual review of what will add, changed ir destroyed 
visulaizing execution plan: graphviz should be installed to visualize the execution plan 

Resource graph : shows the dependency graph. visual representation of states and configurations dependency 

usecases:  supports aws, azure, gcp , multi-tier, for dynamic scheduling for containers , cloud agnostic , cross cloud dependency

core and plugins:
core -- RPC TO plugins
pligins - implentation for service or provisioner 


Terraform CLI Commands:

Terraform INIT : The first command 
The terraform init command initializes a working directory containing Terraform configuration files. 
This is the first command that should be run after writing a new Terraform configuration or cloning an existing one from version control. 
It is safe to run this command multiple times.

pull the provider and modules that are defiined . 

